{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/history/past-prime-ministers/spencer-perceval","content_id":"56d4c3f8-5a66-4819-a317-05ffe775caf5","description":"During a debate on corrupt electoral practices: “I have nothing to say to the nothing that has been said”.","details":{"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Spencer Perceval enjoys the unfortunate distinction of being the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://blog.nationalarchives.gov.uk/blog/the-assassination-of-spencer-perceval/\" class=\"govuk-link\">only British Prime Minister to die at the hands of an assassin.</a> His political career coincided with a period of upheaval created by the French Revolution. Having pursued a successful legal career, he was slowly drawn into politics.</p>\n\n<p>Read more about Spencer Perceval on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://history.blog.gov.uk/2015/10/28/spencer-perceval/\" class=\"govuk-link\">History of government blog</a>.</p>\n</div>","born":"1 November 1762, Audley Square, London","dates_in_office":[{"end_year":1812,"start_year":1809}],"died":"11 May 1812, Lobby of the House of Commons","interesting_facts":"He was the only Prime Minister to be assassinated whilst holding office.\r\n\r\nThe current Conservative MP Henry Bellingham is a direct descendent of the assassin John Bellingham.","major_acts":"Regency Bill 1810: due to George III’s ill health the Prince of Wales was appointed Regent.","political_party":"Tory"},"document_type":"historic_appointment","first_published_at":"2023-01-19T17:38:33+00:00","links":{"available_translations":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/history/past-prime-ministers/spencer-perceval","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/history/past-prime-ministers/spencer-perceval","base_path":"/government/history/past-prime-ministers/spencer-perceval","content_id":"56d4c3f8-5a66-4819-a317-05ffe775caf5","document_type":"historic_appointment","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2023-01-19T17:38:33Z","schema_name":"